# A few aliases to protect us from ourselves:

alias halt="echo You have just attempted to use the \'halt\' command on a physical server.  If you\'re really sure you want to do this, you\'ll have to either delete this alias or use the full path." >& /dev/null
alias poweroff="echo You have just attempted to use the \'poweroff\' command on a physical server.  If you\'re really sure you want to do this, you\'ll have to either delete this alias or use the full path." >& /dev/null
alias shutdown="echo You have just attempted to use the \'shutdown\' command on a physical server.  If you\'re really sure you want to do this, you\'ll have to either delete this alias or use the full path." >& /dev/null
